Florence Dwight Van Patten, appellant, v. State Bank of Chicago, trustee under the will of John H. Dwight, and Pacific Southwest Trust & Savings Bank, executor of the last will and testament of Frances M. Dwight, appellees.Gen. No. 32,079.Heard in the first division of this court for the first district at the October term, 1927.

Matchett, P. J., dissents.

Opinion filed January 30, 1928.Montgomery, Hart & Smith, for appellant; Norman H. Pritchard and John R. Montgomery, of counsel.Bayley, Merrick, Webster & Gregory, for appellees. Mr. Justice O’Connor

delivered the opinion of the court.
